result.execSummary:
The defendant Ronald L Guenther was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Benefit from Trafficking of a Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.051(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, in addition to all other enforcement sanctions available to the court, a civil judgment enforceable by all creditors' remedies shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.

Comply with sexual offender evaluation and any treatment recommendation.
No computer access, no use of Internet or smart phone.
Take medications as prescribed with periodic random testing.
Continue with ongoing psychiatric treatment and evaluations.
Not to possess or consume controlled substances or prescription medication w/out a valid prescription. Inform agent of all current prescriptions and before filling any new prescriptions; keep them in original containers.
Agent and defendant to create a stop smoking program from defendant.
No contact with children under the age of 18 years.
Not to participate in any event supervising children under 18 years.

Submit to DNA sample by 4/2/16.
